  "questions": [
    {
      "text": "A 28-year-old patient presents with a 3-day history of progressive swelling and pain in the right axilla. Physical examination shows a 4-cm fluctuant mass with surrounding erythema and warmth. The patient is afebrile with normal vital signs. Point-of-care ultrasound shows a hypoechoic collection with posterior enhancement adjacent to an artery. The patient has a history of diabetes mellitus and reports similar episodes in the past that required surgical drainage. What is the most appropriate management?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Surgical consultation"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Bedside incision and drainage"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Needle aspiration followed by antibiotics"
        },
        {
          "id": 4,
          "text": "Antibiotic therapy with close follow-up"
        },
        {
          "id": 5,
          "text": "CT scan to evaluate for deeper extension"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 1,
      "solution": "<div><h4 style='color: #34d399; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>A) CORRECT:</h4>Correct -- Surgical consultation is indicated for this axillary <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=aq0QCS&anker=Zc5e4bc5f6a9a7188f4806603b26e8234\" data-learningcard-id=\"aq0QCS\" data-anker=\"Zc5e4bc5f6a9a7188f4806603b26e8234\" data-section-id=\"zc1rUf0\" data-sememe-id=\"yVbdCs\">abscess</a> because of its proximity to important structures such as nerves and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=ZK0ZUS&anker=Zf67f8be5d8e2b577ccc34575c1940df8\" data-learningcard-id=\"ZK0ZUS\" data-anker=\"Zf67f8be5d8e2b577ccc34575c1940df8\" data-section-id=\"WJcPGW0\">arteries</a>, making it inappropriate for bedside drainage. The patient has a history of recurrent <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=aq0QCS&anker=Zc5e4bc5f6a9a7188f4806603b26e8234\" data-learningcard-id=\"aq0QCS\" data-anker=\"Zc5e4bc5f6a9a7188f4806603b26e8234\" data-section-id=\"zc1rUf0\" data-sememe-id=\"yVbdCs\">abscesses</a>, which suggests a complicated <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=aq0QCS&anker=Zc5e4bc5f6a9a7188f4806603b26e8234\" data-learningcard-id=\"aq0QCS\" data-anker=\"Zc5e4bc5f6a9a7188f4806603b26e8234\" data-section-id=\"zc1rUf0\" data-sememe-id=\"yVbdCs\">abscess</a> requiring surgical management.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>B) INCORRECT:</h4>Bedside <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=4F03R3&anker=Zc4b93c7000be544ac7c818622d70b607\" data-learningcard-id=\"4F03R3\" data-anker=\"Zc4b93c7000be544ac7c818622d70b607\" data-sememe-id=\"97WNL50\">incision and drainage</a> are not appropriate for this axillary <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=aq0QCS&anker=Zc5e4bc5f6a9a7188f4806603b26e8234\" data-learningcard-id=\"aq0QCS\" data-anker=\"Zc5e4bc5f6a9a7188f4806603b26e8234\" data-section-id=\"zc1rUf0\" data-sememe-id=\"yVbdCs\">abscess</a>. The <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=cK0a2S&anker=Za39fde93a66b2b4dcd919344fbbbe0a4\" data-learningcard-id=\"cK0a2S\" data-anker=\"Za39fde93a66b2b4dcd919344fbbbe0a4\" data-section-id=\"BJczwW0\" data-sememe-id=\"kP1mUS0\">axilla</a> contains important structures including nerves, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=ZK0ZUS&anker=Zf67f8be5d8e2b577ccc34575c1940df8\" data-learningcard-id=\"ZK0ZUS\" data-anker=\"Zf67f8be5d8e2b577ccc34575c1940df8\" data-section-id=\"WJcPGW0\">arteries</a>, and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=960NMS&anker=Z5fb5bd23c6255d2e24514ab1610448ae\" data-learningcard-id=\"960NMS\" data-anker=\"Z5fb5bd23c6255d2e24514ab1610448ae\" data-section-id=\"ZEcZ8V0\" data-sememe-id=\"yhXdgB\">lymph nodes</a> that could be damaged during bedside drainage. Additionally, the patient's history of recurrent <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=aq0QCS&anker=Zc5e4bc5f6a9a7188f4806603b26e8234\" data-learningcard-id=\"aq0QCS\" data-anker=\"Zc5e4bc5f6a9a7188f4806603b26e8234\" data-section-id=\"zc1rUf0\" data-sememe-id=\"yVbdCs\">abscesses</a> requiring surgical drainage suggests this may be a complicated <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=aq0QCS&anker=Zc5e4bc5f6a9a7188f4806603b26e8234\" data-learningcard-id=\"aq0QCS\" data-anker=\"Zc5e4bc5f6a9a7188f4806603b26e8234\" data-section-id=\"zc1rUf0\" data-sememe-id=\"yVbdCs\">abscess</a>.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>C) INCORRECT:</h4>Needle <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mh0Vef&anker=Z351264651d762713a247d997f6eae551\" data-learningcard-id=\"mh0Vef\" data-anker=\"Z351264651d762713a247d997f6eae551\" data-section-id=\"LZ1wX20\" data-sememe-id=\"xSaEb4\">aspiration</a> is not the preferred treatment for <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=W60PPS&anker=Z84ffaf83e57bb0cc8eb7c50bbc266078\" data-learningcard-id=\"W60PPS\" data-anker=\"Z84ffaf83e57bb0cc8eb7c50bbc266078\">skin</a> and <span data-sememe-id=\"T4c6ic0\">soft tissue</span> <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=aq0QCS&anker=Zc5e4bc5f6a9a7188f4806603b26e8234\" data-learningcard-id=\"aq0QCS\" data-anker=\"Zc5e4bc5f6a9a7188f4806603b26e8234\" data-section-id=\"zc1rUf0\" data-sememe-id=\"yVbdCs\">abscesses</a>.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>D) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mm0VTg&anker=Z4660f53b2b0c85aa3f9ab01bdf3f14f3\" data-learningcard-id=\"mm0VTg\" data-anker=\"Z4660f53b2b0c85aa3f9ab01bdf3f14f3\">Antibiotic therapy</a> alone is insufficient for treating a <span data-sememe-id=\"jBc_0U0\">fluctuant</span> <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=aq0QCS&anker=Zc5e4bc5f6a9a7188f4806603b26e8234\" data-learningcard-id=\"aq0QCS\" data-anker=\"Zc5e4bc5f6a9a7188f4806603b26e8234\" data-section-id=\"zc1rUf0\" data-sememe-id=\"yVbdCs\">abscess</a>. <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=aq0QCS&anker=Zc5e4bc5f6a9a7188f4806603b26e8234\" data-learningcard-id=\"aq0QCS\" data-anker=\"Zc5e4bc5f6a9a7188f4806603b26e8234\" data-section-id=\"zc1rUf0\" data-sememe-id=\"yVbdCs\">Abscesses</a> require drainage for definitive treatment because <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mm0VTg&anker=Z4660f53b2b0c85aa3f9ab01bdf3f14f3\" data-learningcard-id=\"mm0VTg\" data-anker=\"Z4660f53b2b0c85aa3f9ab01bdf3f14f3\">antibiotics</a> have poor penetration into the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=aq0QCS&anker=Zc5e4bc5f6a9a7188f4806603b26e8234\" data-learningcard-id=\"aq0QCS\" data-anker=\"Zc5e4bc5f6a9a7188f4806603b26e8234\" data-section-id=\"zc1rUf0\" data-sememe-id=\"yVbdCs\">abscess</a> cavity and cannot effectively treat organized <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=qh0CUf&anker=Zfdfb82d83e675513c49619bc646fd20c\" data-learningcard-id=\"qh0CUf\" data-anker=\"Zfdfb82d83e675513c49619bc646fd20c\" data-section-id=\"PFcWRV0\" data-sememe-id=\"vIYAeq\">pus</a> collections.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>E) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=KN0UXg&anker=Ze2b9f34cdbf89aef620d4cba111183d1\" data-learningcard-id=\"KN0UXg\" data-anker=\"Ze2b9f34cdbf89aef620d4cba111183d1\" data-sememe-id=\"Fn0gEg\">CT scan</a> is not indicated for this <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xo0EVS&anker=Za466a64a9ff741e0365c57cc1db2aa1b\" data-learningcard-id=\"xo0EVS\" data-anker=\"Za466a64a9ff741e0365c57cc1db2aa1b\" data-section-id=\"h_ccLU0\">superficial</a> <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=aq0QCS&anker=Zc5e4bc5f6a9a7188f4806603b26e8234\" data-learningcard-id=\"aq0QCS\" data-anker=\"Zc5e4bc5f6a9a7188f4806603b26e8234\" data-section-id=\"zc1rUf0\" data-sememe-id=\"yVbdCs\">abscess</a> that has already been confirmed by <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=S70yOh&anker=Ze1c18e0315508a4486624b20d04e368b\" data-learningcard-id=\"S70yOh\" data-anker=\"Ze1c18e0315508a4486624b20d04e368b\" data-sememe-id=\"Lucw7V0\">point-of-care ultrasound</a>. CT does not provide any additional information for guiding management.</div>",
