    {
      "text": "A 28-year-old patient presents with a 3-day history of increasing pain and swelling on the anterior forearm. Physical examination shows a 3.5-cm area of erythema and induration with warmth but no fluctuance. The patient is afebrile with normal vital signs. What is the next most appropriate step in management?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Proceed with incision and drainage based on clinical suspicion"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Prescribe oral antibiotics and arrange follow-up in 24 hours"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Perform needle aspiration to confirm purulent material"
        },
        {
          "id": 4,
          "text": "Obtain point-of-care ultrasound to evaluate the lesion"
        },
        {
          "id": 5,
          "text": "Order CT scan to assess for deep tissue involvement"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 4,
      "solution": "<div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>A) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=4F03R3&anker=Zc4b93c7000be544ac7c818622d70b607\" data-learningcard-id=\"4F03R3\" data-anker=\"Zc4b93c7000be544ac7c818622d70b607\" data-sememe-id=\"97WNL50\">Incision and drainage</a> should not be performed if there is no <span data-sememe-id=\"jBc_0U0\">fluctuance</span>, as premature <span data-sememe-id=\"DT01G2\">incision</span> before <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=aq0QCS&anker=Zc5e4bc5f6a9a7188f4806603b26e8234\" data-learningcard-id=\"aq0QCS\" data-anker=\"Zc5e4bc5f6a9a7188f4806603b26e8234\" data-section-id=\"zc1rUf0\" data-sememe-id=\"yVbdCs\">abscess</a> formation may worsen the infection.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>B) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mm0VTg&anker=Z4660f53b2b0c85aa3f9ab01bdf3f14f3\" data-learningcard-id=\"mm0VTg\" data-anker=\"Z4660f53b2b0c85aa3f9ab01bdf3f14f3\">Antibiotics</a> alone are insufficient for treating an established <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=aq0QCS&anker=Zc5e4bc5f6a9a7188f4806603b26e8234\" data-learningcard-id=\"aq0QCS\" data-anker=\"Zc5e4bc5f6a9a7188f4806603b26e8234\" data-section-id=\"zc1rUf0\" data-sememe-id=\"yVbdCs\">abscess</a>, which requires drainage for definitive management. The size of the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=_405NT&anker=Z2402afe504766ef84f64acad4aaea47b\" data-learningcard-id=\"_405NT\" data-anker=\"Z2402afe504766ef84f64acad4aaea47b\" data-section-id=\"0vXeA-\" data-sememe-id=\"3wYSir\">erythema</a> and induration and the patient's clinical presentation suggest possible <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=aq0QCS&anker=Zc5e4bc5f6a9a7188f4806603b26e8234\" data-learningcard-id=\"aq0QCS\" data-anker=\"Zc5e4bc5f6a9a7188f4806603b26e8234\" data-section-id=\"zc1rUf0\" data-sememe-id=\"yVbdCs\">abscess</a> formation that requires further evaluation rather than <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mm0VTg&anker=Z0d92af1eab239465721da02549c61854\" data-learningcard-id=\"mm0VTg\" data-anker=\"Z0d92af1eab239465721da02549c61854\" data-section-id=\"cubaJv\" data-sememe-id=\"yOadEk\">empiric antibiotic therapy</a>.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>C) INCORRECT:</h4>While needle <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mh0Vef&anker=Z351264651d762713a247d997f6eae551\" data-learningcard-id=\"mh0Vef\" data-anker=\"Z351264651d762713a247d997f6eae551\" data-section-id=\"LZ1wX20\" data-sememe-id=\"xSaEb4\">aspiration</a> can aid diagnosis when <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=HJ0KvS&anker=Z5208bc2efbfd3c982ffbeacf78ebfcb3\" data-learningcard-id=\"HJ0KvS\" data-anker=\"Z5208bc2efbfd3c982ffbeacf78ebfcb3\">physical examination</a> findings are equivocal, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=4n03tg&anker=Z4254d71ea91bb85a18eeeaaf5e7adbef\" data-learningcard-id=\"4n03tg\" data-anker=\"Z4254d71ea91bb85a18eeeaaf5e7adbef\" data-sememe-id=\"fK0kfS\">ultrasound</a> provides superior visualization of the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=aq0QCS&anker=Zc5e4bc5f6a9a7188f4806603b26e8234\" data-learningcard-id=\"aq0QCS\" data-anker=\"Zc5e4bc5f6a9a7188f4806603b26e8234\" data-section-id=\"zc1rUf0\" data-sememe-id=\"yVbdCs\">abscess</a> cavity and can guide subsequent drainage procedures if indicated.</div><div><h4 style='color: #34d399; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>D) CORRECT:</h4>Correct -- <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=S70yOh&anker=Ze1c18e0315508a4486624b20d04e368b\" data-learningcard-id=\"S70yOh\" data-anker=\"Ze1c18e0315508a4486624b20d04e368b\" data-sememe-id=\"Lucw7V0\">Point-of-care ultrasound</a> is indicated to assess for and locate the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=aq0QCS&anker=Zc5e4bc5f6a9a7188f4806603b26e8234\" data-learningcard-id=\"aq0QCS\" data-anker=\"Zc5e4bc5f6a9a7188f4806603b26e8234\" data-section-id=\"zc1rUf0\" data-sememe-id=\"yVbdCs\">abscess</a> cavity when <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=HJ0KvS&anker=Z5208bc2efbfd3c982ffbeacf78ebfcb3\" data-learningcard-id=\"HJ0KvS\" data-anker=\"Z5208bc2efbfd3c982ffbeacf78ebfcb3\">physical examination</a> findings are equivocal. <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=aq0QCS&anker=Zc5e4bc5f6a9a7188f4806603b26e8234\" data-learningcard-id=\"aq0QCS\" data-anker=\"Zc5e4bc5f6a9a7188f4806603b26e8234\" data-section-id=\"zc1rUf0\" data-sememe-id=\"yVbdCs\">Abscesses</a> typically have a <span data-sememe-id=\"iRWJ5O0\">hypoechoic</span> or heterogenous appearance with <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=4n03tg&anker=Z8ffbefc7bfbb0e2d8eb0da8cbc57a316\" data-learningcard-id=\"4n03tg\" data-anker=\"Z8ffbefc7bfbb0e2d8eb0da8cbc57a316\" data-section-id=\"DPX1Sy\" data-sememe-id=\"TYa6oQ\">posterior enhancement</a>.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>E) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=KN0UXg&anker=Ze2b9f34cdbf89aef620d4cba111183d1\" data-learningcard-id=\"KN0UXg\" data-anker=\"Ze2b9f34cdbf89aef620d4cba111183d1\" data-sememe-id=\"Fn0gEg\">CT scan</a> is not indicated for simple <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=W60PPS&anker=Z84ffaf83e57bb0cc8eb7c50bbc266078\" data-learningcard-id=\"W60PPS\" data-anker=\"Z84ffaf83e57bb0cc8eb7c50bbc266078\">skin</a> and <span data-sememe-id=\"T4c6ic0\">soft tissue</span> <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=aq0QCS&anker=Zc5e4bc5f6a9a7188f4806603b26e8234\" data-learningcard-id=\"aq0QCS\" data-anker=\"Zc5e4bc5f6a9a7188f4806603b26e8234\" data-section-id=\"zc1rUf0\" data-sememe-id=\"yVbdCs\">abscesses</a>. This approach would delay appropriate treatment and increase health care costs without providing any clinical benefit.</div>",
